 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Rotational Leadership Program Comcast 16,770 reviews Philadelphia, PA Comcast 16,770 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job Summary 
Responsible for cross-functional projects in critical areas of the business while developing relationships and experiences designed to develop a cadre of future leaders in an innovative, technology enterprise. Cohort and individualized leadership development are key components of the 2-year experience. 
Job Description 
We are recruiting for the next class of the Comcast NBCUniversal Rotational Leadership Program for leadership participants. RLP members work on cross-functional projects in critical areas of the business while developing relationships and experiences designed to develop a cadre of future leaders in an innovative, technology enterprise. RLP builds versatile strategic leaders with an expansive, connected networking that amplifies business results and partnerships. Current projects include areas such as Artificial Intelligence, Digital Media, Product Development, Research, Advanced Advertising and Strategy. Cohort and individualized leadership development are key components of the 2-year experience. 
Program Elements 
Critical High Impact Projects 
Structured, customized experiences on high profile projects. 
Opportunity to gain exposure to several areas of the business within Comcast and NBCUniversal. 
Rotations require mobility to various locations. 
Leadership Development 
Targeted development leveraging internal executives and specialized experiences. 
Exposure to senior leadership through rotations, internal consulting projects and access to executive steering committee members. 
Involvement in related industry organizations and conferences. 
Cadre, Coaching and Mentorship 
In addition to individual experiences, participants come together as a team throughout the program. Cohort structure creates an exceptional peer learning opportunities, offering project collaboration and team problem solving. 
Advocates, leadership program managers and rotation hosts provide coaching and performance feedback. 
Participants also have the opportunity to contribute to continual program enhancements and mentor future participants. 
Candidate Profile 
Innovative leaders seeking to make a significant contribution and business impact in a global technology company. 
Track record of academic curiosity with an advanced degree (MBA or Technology Focused preferred) 
5-7 years relevant work experience in dynamic environment (e.g. technology, start-ups, consulting, military, etc.) 
Drives inclusion and diversity by creating a culture of understanding, unique contributions, broad perspectives, trust, transparency, and empowerment 
Background working in agile, diverse environments 
Business savvy, situational team leadership 
Moves nimbly between strategy and execution 
Fosters strategic thinking within a team 
Leverages data analytics and researching capabilities 
Communicates effectively at all levels in a variety of settings 
Exhibits influential presence 
Self-starter, able to work independently and track record of taking initiative 
Passionate about innovation and technology in our industry 
Global experience of interest 
Geographic flexibility 
Employees at all levels are expected to: 
Understand our Operating Principles; make them the guidelines for how you do your job. 
Own the customer experience - think and act in ways that put our customers first, give them seamless digital options at every touchpoint, and make them promoters of our products and services. 
Know your stuff - be enthusiastic learners, users and advocates of our game-changing technology, products and services, especially our digital tools and experiences. 
Win as a team - make big things happen by working together and being open to new ideas. 
Be an active part of the Net Promoter System - a way of working that brings more employee and customer feedback into the company - by joining huddles, making call backs and helping us elevate opportunities to do better for our customers. 
Drive results and growth. 
Respect and promote inclusion & diversity. 
Do what's right for each other, our customers, investors and our communities. 
